text:
A Feast to Remember ‚Äì Perfect for Celebrations! üéâ

If you're looking for a dining experience that takes your taste buds on a journey across China (with a delicious stop in Spain!), this is the place.

üî• Bold Hunan flavors bring the heat, while green chillies from Shandong pack a punch that's both spicy and addictive. The Iberian pork from Spain is melt-in-your-mouth tender ‚Äî a rich, smoky surprise among the Chinese classics. Don't miss the crunchy white fungus from Yunnan, which adds a refreshing texture, or the sweet, pearly white rice from Northern China ‚Äì so good you'll want a second bowl (or third).

‚ú® And did we mention the free-flow ice cream and endless cracker snacks? It's a nostalgic dream come true.

Whether you're here for the food or to celebrate something special, this spot has the right mix of vibrant flavors and good vibes. Ideal for birthdays ‚Äì or any excuse to treat yourself! üéÇüçΩÔ∏è

name: Laugh Love
text:
Disappointed with the service despite good food.

We visited Xiang Xiang on 28 June around 11:30am for lunch and stayed for about an hour. While making payment, I was carrying my restless toddler when the cashier started explaining a promotion. She mentioned that our bill was quite high and said we could enjoy a promotion immediately. I didn‚Äôt fully catch the details and assumed it was about collecting points or getting a small discount. She then said that if I paid with a DBS Mastercard, I‚Äôd receive a $10 voucher for future use. I agreed and passed her my card.

To my shock, the receipt showed a $300 charge ‚Äî our actual bill was only $144. Only then did I realise she had signed me up for a $300 dining credit package without clearly explaining it. I immediately told her I did not want it and requested a refund. She said she would help me after assisting the customers behind me. I waited, but she didn‚Äôt follow up. I had to go back to her, and she handed me a refund receipt, saying I would receive the refund within 12 hours. I also returned the $10 voucher and told her clearly that I was doing so, to avoid any misunderstanding ‚Äî she didn‚Äôt acknowledge this and responded with a very poor attitude.

To add to the frustration, I needed to settle my actual bill ‚Äî but she asked me to pay $157, which was more than the original $144. I had to show her the original bill to ensure I was paying the correct amount. Again, no apology, no proper explanation. I didn‚Äôt catch her name, but she wore a ‚Äúone-star staff‚Äù badge. It feels like they‚Äôre trying to deliver Haidilao-style service, but this staff‚Äôs attitude and communication were far from it.

The food itself was good, but the unclear promotion, poor communication, and lack of professionalism really marred the experience. I hope the management takes this seriously and improves staff training on both service and clarity of promotions.

reviewContext/Parking: Try to come before 6pm for ample parking lots.

text:
Five Star Dinning Experience at Xiang Xiang Hunan Restaurant (Pasir Ris Mall)

My recent visit to celebrate our son's birthday was nothing short of exceptional, leaving us thoroughly impressed by the impeccable service, swift delivery of delicious food, and the incredibly thoughtful gestures that made our special occasion truly unforgettable.

From the moment we were seated, the service at Xiang Xiang was truly immaculate. The staff were attentive, polite, and incredibly efficient. Our orders were taken promptly, and to our pleasant surprise, the dishes arrived at our table with remarkable speed, each kept wonderfully warm by a clever mobile gas cooker placed beneath. This ensured that every bite, from the first to the last, was as enjoyable as if it had just left the kitchen.

We ordered straight from the list of signature dishes  The Hunan Stir-fry Pork was delicious though the sight of the green chilli had raised my hope of getting a greater kick of spiciness. The Golden Broth Sour and Spicy Fish was unique with the lemon slices and fish slices bathed in a golden broth that was citrusy and sweet all at once. We enjoyed the earthy flavours of the Bamboo Shoot Stir-fry with Bacon Pork that paired well with rice. The simple yet comforting Hand-shredded Cabbage as well as Sour and Spicy Potatoes provided a delightful textural contrast. The Olive Green Bean Delight was alright. The Dry Tossed Vermicelli Pot was a flavourful and satisfying noodle dish, and the 18-Second Angus Beef Stir-fry was well liked by my family. incredibly tender and packed with flavour.

What truly elevated our experience beyond the array of food was the genuine warmth and thoughtfulness shown towards our son's birthday celebration. The restaurant offered us longevity noodles, which we kindly declined as we had ordered quite a feast.

To our surprise and delight, the staff went above and beyond by creating a makeshift birthday "cake" out of ice creams! They then came over to our table, singing a heartfelt birthday song, making our son feel incredibly special.

This unexpected and incredibly kind gesture truly showcased the exceptional hospitality at Xiang Xiang Hunan Restaurant.

Highly Recommended!
title: Xiang Xiang Hunan Cuisine @ Pasir Ris Mall

Impressive Recovery Service at XiangXiang
I recently ordered grab food for XiangXiang and had a mix-up with my order, but their quick and prompt recovery service truly impressed me. After receiving the wrong dish, I sent a message to the staff, and they immediately apologized and took action without hesitation.
Within minutes, the manager whatsapped me to address the issue personally. They offered to replace the wrong order and even provided a complimentary appetizer as a gesture of goodwill. The replacement dish arrived swiftly, and it was absolutely delicious!
Not only did they handle the situation efficiently, but their attentive customer service also made a positive impression. It's clear that XiangXiang values their customers and strives to deliver a great dining experience, even when mistakes happen.
Overall, I highly recommend XiangXiang not just for their tasty food, but also for their excellent service recovery. I will definitely be eating more often !
